Kano State Government has declared tomorrow Thursday, August 20, 2020, as public holiday to mark the new Islamic year 1442, After Hijrah (AH). In a statement signed by Commissioner for Information, Malam Muhammadu Garba,  Governor Abdullahi Umar Ganduje urged Muslims in the state and across the country to use the occasion for sober reflection. Ganduje advocated special supplication for continued peace, prosperity and general development of the state and the entire country. The governor sought offer of prayers for Allahâ€™s intervention over the current economic hardship being experienced by the people, occasioned by the ravaging COVID-19 pandemic as well as a new year full of happiness and prosperity. Ganduje called on the citizenry to always fear God in all their dealings, imbibe tolerance and live peacefully with one another as always inculcated by Islam.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .